  "excerpt": "<p>This tutorial covers using a metrics alias where you may have 1 unique metric or KPI that has an abbreviation or multiple names.</p>",
  "content_html": "\n<p>This tutorial covers using a metrics alias where you may have 1 unique metric or KPI that has an abbreviation or multiple names. A highly common scenario in any enterprise is having multiple names or terms for a single metric or KPI. There are plenty of reasonable cases where this could occur. <a href=\"http://salesforce-metrics-glossary/\" title=\"Metrics Glossary\">DataTools Pro metrics glossary</a> covers this using aliases.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Common reasons why you could have multiple names for 1 metric:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Abbreviations or short names that business or technology professionals use.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Evolution of an enterprises taxonomies and definitions</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Mergers and acquisitions</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Consolidation of teams and new leadership</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Refinement in performance management practice </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/datatools-for-salesforce\" title=\"https://datatoolspro.com\">DataTools Pro</a> provides metric aliases, so you can define and change the definitive name of your metrics over time while retaining all of the aliases.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f5f8f7\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"391\" height=\"348\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-2.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9473 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f5f8f7; width:275px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-2.png 391w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-2-300x267.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 391px) 100vw, 391px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How does DataTools Pro use aliases?</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-3 gb-3-col-equal\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-medium-font-size\">Reference tool<br></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>As a reference tool, DataTools Pro users have constant visibility over aliases within the metrics table or within the metrics details side panel.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\">Change management tracking</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>With DataTools Pro metric chnage tracking, we allow you to retain the history as your metrics and KPIs evolve</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\">AI enhanced metric Analyst<br></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When you use DataTools Pro Metric Analyst we utilize all metrics aliases to compare and interpret when metrics are brand new or simply new variations of metrics you already track.</p>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Adding or Editing DataTools Pro Aliases</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Add or Edit Alias from the Metrics table</strong>:</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Click the &#8220;+&#8221; button from the Aliases column OR click on the name of an Alias</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f9f9f8\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f9f9f8;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"292\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-3-1024x292.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9474 has-transparency\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-3-1024x292.png 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-3-300x86.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-3-768x219.png 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-3.png 1111w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Enter your Alias name and click &#8220;Add&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f1f7f6\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f1f7f6;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"346\" height=\"164\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-5.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9476 has-transparency\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-5.png 346w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-5-300x142.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 346px) 100vw, 346px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>3. You can modify your Alias as primary which impacts how your metric will appear in DataTools Pro.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f3f7f7\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f3f7f7;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"360\" height=\"258\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-6.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9477 has-transparency\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-6.png 360w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-6-300x215.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Add or Edit Alias from the Metrics Side Panel</strong>:</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can complete the same steps prior by clicking the &#8220;Edit&#8221; button to the left of the title &#8220;Metrics Name and Aliases&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f5eeee\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f5eeee;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"288\" height=\"119\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-4.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9475 has-transparency\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Updating Primary Metrics Alias</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The &#8220;Primary&#8221; alias is what DataTools Pro uses to visually represent the name of your metric throughout the user experience, with the notion that the primary represents what is most commonly accepted for your orginazation. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Tracking Metrics Alias Changes</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When metrics aliases change, you can view those changes in the metrics audit logs.</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Click on the history icon located on the metrics page above the metrics table.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"e5f0ed\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" style=\"--dominant-color: #e5f0ed;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"580\" height=\"134\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-8.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9479 has-transparency\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-8.png 580w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-8-300x69.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Select &#8220;Alias&#8221; within the Filter by Action dropdown. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f9fafa\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f9fafa;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"408\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-7-1024x408.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9478 has-transparency\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-7-1024x408.png 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-7-300x120.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-7-768x306.png 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/image-7.png 1129w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n"
